    CustomList
    This class creates an ArrayList of players to be displayed as a custom view.
    CustomList2

    This class allows the user to scan a QRCode to log into their account from another device.

    This class helps in plotting the latitude longitude on the map.
    GlobalAllPlayers
    This class makes allPlayers a global variable to grant access to all the players in the game.
    ID
    This class is used to make a unique ID for a QR.
    MainActivity
    This activity is responsible for displaying the main user interface when the user first opens the app, and calls activities accordingly with the users input.
    MyScans
    This activity displays a list of all the user's scans.
    NewUser
    This activity opens if a user does not already have an existing account, and is responsible for creating a new user account for the user.
    OtherPlayerListAdapter
    This class acts as an adapter for OtherPlayerList list.
    OtherPlayerProfile

    This is an Adapter class for custom listview of player.
    OwnerMenu
    This class acts as a menu for the owner and displays appropriate owner options.
    ownerPlayerProfile
    This activity makes a player profile listview that owner can select and delete.
    Player
    This activity is responsible for creating an object of type Player, that represents an instance of a player in the game.
    PlayerProfile
    This class displays the user's information, and also allows the option to generate a QR code to log into their account on a different device.
    PlayerRanking

    This class displays the current user's information in respect to all players in the Database.

    Score
    This class computes a QR code's score.
    SingletonPlayer
    This class represents a global instance of the current player.
    UserMenu
    This activity is responsible for displaying the main user menu.
    ViewImage
    This activity displays the image associated to a QR code.
    ViewQRCode
    This activity displays the information on a QR code and it allows the user to add new comments or open a picture associated to it if there is one.
